.TH "thermal_emergency_poweroff_func" 9 "thermal_emergency_poweroff_func" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
thermal_emergency_poweroff_func \- emergency poweroff work after a known delay
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" thermal_emergency_poweroff_func
.BI "(struct work_struct *work "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "work" 12
work_struct associated with the emergency poweroff function
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is called in very critical situations to force
a kernel poweroff after a configurable timeout value.
